.TH _printf 3 "April 2026" "" "holbertonschool-printf"
.SH NAME
_printf \- formatted output conversion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function produces output according to a format string and writes the output to the standard output.

The format string is a character string composed of zero or more directives.
This function handles the following conversion specifiers:
.PP
.B %c
for printing a character
.PP
.B %s
for printing a string
.PP
.B %%
for printing a percent sign
.PP
.B %d
for printing a decimal integer
.PP
.B %i
for printing an integer
.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon successful return,
.B _printf
returns the number of characters printed, excluding the terminating null byte.

If an error occurs, the function returns -1.

.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
_printf("Character: %c\en", 'H');
_printf("String: %s\en", "Hello");
_printf("Percent: %%\en");
_printf("Number: %d\en", 123);
.EE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3)
